    <content><![CDATA[<h1 id="Introduction"><a href="#Introduction" class="headerlink" title="Introduction"></a>Introduction</h1><h3 id="Python-is-the-first-computer-programming-language-I-learn-so-that-I-have-some-thoughts-to-share-about-my-experience-Compared-with-human-mind-in-some-ways-computer-works-the-same-Most-of-the-programs-I-learn-so-far-work-based-on-two-logic-True-or-False-and-if-or-else-Computer-will-make-choice-according-to-the-content-we-type-in-just-like-human-However-I-want-to-talk-more-about-differences-between-computer-language-and-human-language-When-we-give-somebody-an-order-we-focus-on-the-thesis-details-are-not-so-important-Nevertheless-it-is-totally-different-in-computer-language-Every-detail-must-be-correct-in-the-code-we-type-such-as-the-indented-block-the-symbol-the-format-of-your-code-and-even-a-blank-If-there-is-only-one-mistake-the-whole-program-will-not-work-In-the-other-hand-symbols-in-computer-language-are-have-different-meaning-compared-with-it-in-math-For-example-when-we-want-two-Boolean-values-equal-we-need-to-type-‘-’-instead-of-‘-’-As-a-beginner-I-have-a-lot-of-trouble-to-use-correct-symbols-when-I-write-code"><a href="#Python-is-the-first-computer-programming-language-I-learn-so-that-I-have-some-thoughts-to-share-about-my-experience-Compared-with-human-mind-in-some-ways-computer-works-the-same-Most-of-the-programs-I-learn-so-far-work-based-on-two-logic-True-or-False-and-if-or-else-Computer-will-make-choice-according-to-the-content-we-type-in-just-like-human-However-I-want-to-talk-more-about-differences-between-computer-language-and-human-language-When-we-give-somebody-an-order-we-focus-on-the-thesis-details-are-not-so-important-Nevertheless-it-is-totally-different-in-computer-language-Every-detail-must-be-correct-in-the-code-we-type-such-as-the-indented-block-the-symbol-the-format-of-your-code-and-even-a-blank-If-there-is-only-one-mistake-the-whole-program-will-not-work-In-the-other-hand-symbols-in-computer-language-are-have-different-meaning-compared-with-it-in-math-For-example-when-we-want-two-Boolean-values-equal-we-need-to-type-‘-’-instead-of-‘-’-As-a-beginner-I-have-a-lot-of-trouble-to-use-correct-symbols-when-I-write-code" class="headerlink" title="Python is the first computer programming language I learn so that I have some thoughts to share about my experience. Compared with human mind, in some ways computer works the same. Most of the programs I learn so far work based on two logic: True or False and if or else. Computer will make choice according to the content we type in just like human. However, I want to talk more about differences between computer language and human language. When we give somebody an order, we focus on the thesis, details are not so important. Nevertheless, it is totally different in computer language. Every detail must be correct in the code we type, such as the indented block, the symbol, the format of your code and even a blank. If there is only one mistake, the whole program will not work. In the other hand, symbols in computer language are have different meaning compared with it in math. For example, when we want two Boolean values equal, we need to type ‘==’ instead of ‘=’. As a beginner, I have a lot of trouble to use correct symbols when I write code."></a><em>Python is the first computer programming language I learn so that I have some thoughts to share about my experience. Compared with human mind, in some ways computer works the same. Most of the programs I learn so far work based on two logic: True or False and if or else. Computer will make choice according to the content we type in just like human. However, I want to talk more about differences between computer language and human language. When we give somebody an order, we focus on the thesis, details are not so important. Nevertheless, it is totally different in computer language. Every detail must be correct in the code we type, such as the indented block, the symbol, the format of your code and even a blank. If there is only one mistake, the whole program will not work. In the other hand, symbols in computer language are have different meaning compared with it in math. For example, when we want two Boolean values equal, we need to type ‘==’ instead of ‘=’. As a beginner, I have a lot of trouble to use correct symbols when I write code.</em></h3><h1 id="Impression"><a href="#Impression" class="headerlink" title="Impression"></a>Impression</h1><h3 id="I-used-to-have-a-question-after-a-few-weeks’-learning-Computer-is-used-to-help-us-work-more-convenient-and-quickly-but-why-I-seems-to-spend-more-time-on-writing-a-code-I-can-finish-it-much-more-quickly-by-myself-The-problem-bothered-me-until-the-teacher-gave-us-an-example-A-teacher-wants-to-know-10-students-average-mark-after-he-put-10-results-in-I-just-spend-3-minutes-to-finish-the-code-instead-of-adding-10-marks-and-dividing-10-In-my-opinion-computer-is-just-a-like-a-little-child-which-only-can-do-any-complex-calculation-and-never-forget-things-In-order-to-let-him-to-solve-difficult-questions-I-need-to-teach-him-how-to-do-it-and-I-only-teach-him-once-After-that-I-just-need-to-type-my-data-and-he-will-give-me-the-answer-I-think-that-is-the-reason-we-learn-the-different-computer-language"><a href="#I-used-to-have-a-question-after-a-few-weeks’-learning-Computer-is-used-to-help-us-work-more-convenient-and-quickly-but-why-I-seems-to-spend-more-time-on-writing-a-code-I-can-finish-it-much-more-quickly-by-myself-The-problem-bothered-me-until-the-teacher-gave-us-an-example-A-teacher-wants-to-know-10-students-average-mark-after-he-put-10-results-in-I-just-spend-3-minutes-to-finish-the-code-instead-of-adding-10-marks-and-dividing-10-In-my-opinion-computer-is-just-a-like-a-little-child-which-only-can-do-any-complex-calculation-and-never-forget-things-In-order-to-let-him-to-solve-difficult-questions-I-need-to-teach-him-how-to-do-it-and-I-only-teach-him-once-After-that-I-just-need-to-type-my-data-and-he-will-give-me-the-answer-I-think-that-is-the-reason-we-learn-the-different-computer-language" class="headerlink" title="I used to have a question after a few weeks’ learning: Computer is used to help us work more convenient and quickly, but why I seems to spend more time on writing a code? I can finish it much more quickly by myself. The problem bothered me until the teacher gave us an example: A teacher wants to know 10 students average mark after he put 10 results in. I just spend 3 minutes to finish the code instead of adding 10 marks and dividing 10. In my opinion, computer is just a like a little child which only can do any complex calculation and never forget things. In order to let him to solve difficult questions, I need to teach him how to do it and I only teach him once. After that, I just need to type my data and he will give me the answer. I think that is the reason we learn the different computer language."></a><em>I used to have a question after a few weeks’ learning: Computer is used to help us work more convenient and quickly, but why I seems to spend more time on writing a code? I can finish it much more quickly by myself. The problem bothered me until the teacher gave us an example: A teacher wants to know 10 students average mark after he put 10 results in. I just spend 3 minutes to finish the code instead of adding 10 marks and dividing 10. In my opinion, computer is just a like a little child which only can do any complex calculation and never forget things. In order to let him to solve difficult questions, I need to teach him how to do it and I only teach him once. After that, I just need to type my data and he will give me the answer. I think that is the reason we learn the different computer language.</em></h3><h3 id="A-flowchart-is-an-important-step-in-writing-a-program-Flowcharts-show-the-logic-you-need-to-write-a-program-in-a-simple-way-helping-us-tease-out-the-key-steps-There-are-only-two-sections-of-the-flow-chart-the-execution-section-and-the-judgment-section-Here-is-a-flowchart-I-drew-while-writing-the-program"><a href="#A-flowchart-is-an-important-step-in-writing-a-program-Flowcharts-show-the-logic-you-need-to-write-a-program-in-a-simple-way-helping-us-tease-out-the-key-steps-There-are-only-two-sections-of-the-flow-chart-the-execution-section-and-the-judgment-section-Here-is-a-flowchart-I-drew-while-writing-the-program" class="headerlink" title="A flowchart is an important step in writing a program. Flowcharts show the logic you need to write a program in a simple way, helping us tease out the key steps. There are only two sections of the flow chart: the execution section and the judgment section. Here is a flowchart I drew while writing the program."></a><em>A flowchart is an important step in writing a program. Flowcharts show the logic you need to write a program in a simple way, helping us tease out the key steps. There are only two sections of the flow chart: the execution section and the judgment section. Here is a flowchart I drew while writing the program.</em></h3><h1 id="Examples"><a href="#Examples" class="headerlink" title="Examples"></a>Examples</h1><h3 id="Now-I-am-going-to-introduce-some-program-that-I-write"><a href="#Now-I-am-going-to-introduce-some-program-that-I-write" class="headerlink" title="Now I am going to introduce some program that I write."></a>Now I am going to introduce some program that I write.</h3><h4 id="First-program-is-help-customers-order-their-food"><a href="#First-program-is-help-customers-order-their-food" class="headerlink" title="First program is help customers order their food"></a>First program is help customers order their food</h4><figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">menu &#x3D; &#123;&#39;1&#39;: &#39;CAFE&#39;, &#39;2&#39;: &#39;MILK ITEA&#39;, &#39;3&#39;: &#39;ICE CREAM&#39;, &#39;4&#39;: &#39;REPORT&#39;&#125;</span><br><span class="line">while True:</span><br><span class="line">    print (&#39;enter a number: (blank to quit)&#39;)</span><br><span class="line">    number &#x3D; input()</span><br><span class="line">    if number &#x3D;&#x3D; &#39;&#39;:</span><br><span class="line">        break</span><br><span class="line">    if number in menu: </span><br><span class="line">        print(&#39;HOW MANY DO YOU WANT?&#39;)</span><br><span class="line">        amount &#x3D; input()</span><br><span class="line">        print ( amount  + menu[number])</span><br><span class="line">    else:</span><br><span class="line">        print(&#39;I do not have this food&#39;)</span><br><span class="line">        print(&#39;We have CAFE  MILK TEA ICE CREAM OR REPORT&#39;)</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>

<h4 id="Second-one-is-to-calculate-the-monthly-payment-in-a-bank"><a href="#Second-one-is-to-calculate-the-monthly-payment-in-a-bank" class="headerlink" title="Second one is to calculate the monthly payment in a bank"></a>Second one is to calculate the monthly payment in a bank</h4><figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">annual_interest_rate &#x3D; float(input(&#39;please input the annual interest rate: &#39;))</span><br><span class="line">duration &#x3D; int(input(&#39;please input the duration: &#39;))</span><br><span class="line">r &#x3D; annual_interest_rate&#x2F;12</span><br><span class="line">n &#x3D; duration</span><br><span class="line">if r &#x3D;&#x3D; 0:</span><br><span class="line">    monthly_payment &#x3D; principle&#x2F;n</span><br><span class="line">else:</span><br><span class="line">    monthly_payment &#x3D; principle*r*(1+r)**n&#x2F;((1+r)**n-1)</span><br><span class="line">print(&#39;monthly payment is:&#39;, monthly_payment)</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>

